SIMPLE: hermaphroditical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hermaphroditical
<hw>Her*maph`ro*dit"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Partaking of the characteristics of
both sexes; having male and female reproductive organs in the same plant
or animal; characterized by hermaphroditism. Opposite of
<contr>dioecious</contr>.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>--
<wordforms><wf>Her*maph`ro*dit"ic*al*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> monoecious, monecious, hermaphrodite.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <fld>(Botany)</fld>
<def>having pistils and stamens in the same flower. Opposite of
<ant>diclinous</ant>.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> monoclinous.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hermaphroditism</ent>⟦br⟧
